  "_comment": "Gravitas solar system data. Orbital elements from NASA JPL Horizons. Spin-axis data from NAIF pck00011.tpc evaluated at J2000 where available; Eris uses the published Dysnomia orbit-pole proxy, while Makemake currently uses an explicit zero-tilt orbit-relative fallback because no unique absolute pole solution is published. Spin-physics is opt-in: inertiaFactor is seeded where a stable literature value is already well known, while k2OverQ is seeded only for bodies with a direct observational or mission-constrained estimate; the remaining bodies stay unseeded or at zero until a defensible dissipative source is curated.",
